WEBVTT

00:02.900 --> 00:04.633
He was set upon?

00:04.634 --> 00:05.932
Homo bashed.

00:05.933 --> 00:08.032
It's all right, Harry.

00:08.032 --> 00:09.733
It's Sarah.

00:09.734 --> 00:12.766
He was beaten to within
an inch of his life.

00:12.767 --> 00:15.666
He can recover here without
any stigma attached to him.

00:15.667 --> 00:17.299
I doubt George will thank you.

00:17.300 --> 00:18.666
Nor James.

00:18.667 --> 00:19.932
Relax.

00:19.933 --> 00:22.899
If your dubious virtue
was in any danger,

00:22.900 --> 00:25.865
you'd be on your back
already, moaning for more.

00:25.866 --> 00:28.132
Has he behaved
inappropriately towards you?

00:28.133 --> 00:29.399
(SIGHS)

00:29.400 --> 00:31.099
What did he do?

00:31.100 --> 00:32.566
(SOBS)

00:32.567 --> 00:33.999
Let's set a date.

00:34.000 --> 00:35.266
Husband and wife.

00:35.267 --> 00:36.232
Yes.

00:36.233 --> 00:37.366
(LAUGHS)

00:37.367 --> 00:40.700
Anna wants you both to know she
doesn't believe the rumors.

00:40.701 --> 00:41.666
What rumors?

00:41.667 --> 00:43.599
Oh, there are some real
gossipy types around here.

00:43.600 --> 00:45.299
People are saying things about us?

00:45.300 --> 00:46.800
Oh, who cares?

00:46.801 --> 00:48.801
They're all liars anyway.

00:49.467 --> 00:51.066
Gather the staff.

00:51.067 --> 00:53.666
The prime minister dines this Wednesday.

00:53.667 --> 00:57.600
Despite everything, she has
proven her worth, hasn't she?

00:58.300 --> 01:00.066
The prime minister <i>is</i> a coup.

01:00.067 --> 01:01.800
But I will keep an eye on her.

01:01.801 --> 01:04.032
I suspect a crowd at the gates.

01:04.033 --> 01:05.433
Make sure it's vetted.

01:05.434 --> 01:07.467
We don't want any left-wing outbursts.

01:07.966 --> 01:09.366
There'll be none of that.

01:09.367 --> 01:11.299
I'd like you to move along peacefully.

01:11.300 --> 01:12.299
- I...
- Go on. Get.

01:12.300 --> 01:14.299
Your name is on a list of troublemakers.

01:14.300 --> 01:16.166
She may well have secured
George's election

01:16.167 --> 01:17.132
with this dinner.

01:17.133 --> 01:18.832
Let's go back tomorrow, then.

01:18.833 --> 01:20.866
Timing, my darling.

01:21.434 --> 01:22.832
Timing is everything.

01:22.833 --> 01:23.832
You're returning?

01:23.833 --> 01:26.366
At half past 6:00 tonight. Precisely.

01:26.367 --> 01:27.333
That's very specific.

01:27.334 --> 01:29.832
Oh, it's for a very specific reason.

01:29.833 --> 01:31.832
You're looking forward to it, then?

01:31.833 --> 01:33.832
Oh, you have no idea.

01:34.551 --> 01:38.745
- sync and corrections by Mr.C -
- www.addic7ed.com -

01:43.067 --> 01:44.999
(BIRDS CHIRPING)

01:45.000 --> 01:46.667
(GRUNTS)

01:48.000 --> 01:54.074
Advertise your product or brand here
contact www.OpenSubtitles.org today

01:55.600 --> 01:57.833
(INDISTINCT CONVERSATIONS)

02:19.367 --> 02:21.300
REGINA: You're starting early.

02:22.634 --> 02:24.166
My wound's playing up.

02:24.167 --> 02:25.932
Can I fetch some morphine?

02:25.933 --> 02:28.132
I-I kept one of the
bottles, just in case.

02:28.133 --> 02:29.434
You shouldn't have.

02:30.300 --> 02:33.366
This perverse need to suffer.

02:33.367 --> 02:34.399
Just for tonight?

02:34.400 --> 02:35.865
I need a clear head.

02:35.866 --> 02:38.766
He says, gulping whiskey.

02:38.767 --> 02:40.666
We can't have you
either drunk or wincing

02:40.667 --> 02:42.599
in front of the prime minister.

02:42.600 --> 02:44.467
I'm done with that stuff.

02:46.233 --> 02:48.032
I know why you're abstaining.

02:48.033 --> 02:51.900
You'd rather suffer than risk
dropping your guard again.

02:53.500 --> 02:55.634
Was touching me so loathsome?

02:59.467 --> 03:03.900
If I wasn't befuddled, it
wouldn't have happened.

03:06.100 --> 03:07.300
Here.

03:10.900 --> 03:12.499
You still have feelings for Mrs.
Nordmann.

03:12.500 --> 03:13.766
- I understand.
- I'd rather you didn't...

03:13.767 --> 03:16.334
But you are entertaining
the prime minister.

03:17.900 --> 03:19.965
You deserve more than
being the second choice

03:19.966 --> 03:21.067
of a country nurse.

03:23.500 --> 03:25.567
Do you value yourself so little?

03:29.233 --> 03:32.067
(DOWN-TEMPO MUSIC PLAYING)

03:35.567 --> 03:38.233
(INDISTINCT CONVERSATIONS)

03:41.866 --> 03:43.099
Rose.

03:43.100 --> 03:44.833
Mrs. Poletti.

03:48.634 --> 03:50.800
- I'm so embarrassed.
- Oh, don't be.

03:50.801 --> 03:53.999
I just wanted to say that our
dinner invitation is genuine.

03:54.000 --> 03:55.099
When you're free.

03:55.100 --> 03:56.666
Thank you.

03:56.667 --> 03:58.099
The lessons?

03:58.100 --> 03:59.232
Let's do them together.

03:59.233 --> 04:02.132
My Italian could always
do with some improvement.

04:02.133 --> 04:05.299
I hope I find a man like Mr.
Poletti one day.

04:05.300 --> 04:06.499
I'm sure you will.

04:06.500 --> 04:08.534
You're both so lucky.

04:12.033 --> 04:13.933
(BIRDS CHIRPING)

04:24.701 --> 04:27.299
Small sips will leave you pain-free

04:27.300 --> 04:29.833
and much sharper than too much of that.

04:34.300 --> 04:36.833
I promise not to ravish you.

04:39.900 --> 04:42.701
(DOWN-TEMPO MUSIC PLAYING)

04:55.618 --> 04:57.617
Oh, someone has to mind the shop.

04:57.618 --> 04:59.817
But, Valda, you go if you want to.

04:59.818 --> 05:01.517
To see Menzies?

05:01.518 --> 05:03.484
I'd rather poke my eye out with a fork.

05:07.918 --> 05:09.684
JACK: Poor old Doris got a rough trot.

05:09.685 --> 05:11.183
We're going to support her.

05:11.184 --> 05:13.884
CAROLYN: For George's sake,
don't do anything foolish.

05:13.885 --> 05:15.317
Like beating the living daylights

05:15.318 --> 05:16.617
out of Sir bloody Richard?

05:16.618 --> 05:18.717
(VEHICLE APPROACHING)

05:18.718 --> 05:21.083
Mother knows what's happened.

05:21.084 --> 05:22.750
She's on her way down.

05:22.751 --> 05:23.750
How?

05:23.751 --> 05:25.550
It just came out.

05:25.551 --> 05:26.984
Are you all right?

05:26.985 --> 05:28.550
I'm fine.

05:28.551 --> 05:32.018
But I doubt he will be... or Regina.

05:32.785 --> 05:35.550
You really do have a
novelist's imagination.

05:35.551 --> 05:38.483
It's obvious you sent
Rose over to tempt him.

05:38.484 --> 05:39.517
To the paranoid, perhaps.

05:39.518 --> 05:42.017
And when she didn't, you
implied that she had.

05:42.018 --> 05:44.116
You're wasting your time.

05:44.117 --> 05:47.550
We're in love... unlike you and Father.

05:47.551 --> 05:48.850
I adore George, and...

05:48.851 --> 05:50.250
You're expedient.

05:50.251 --> 05:52.018
He simply tolerates you.

05:59.484 --> 06:01.318
You loathsome minx.

06:01.885 --> 06:04.751
If you weren't so pathetic,
you'd be laughable.

06:07.084 --> 06:10.116
I have invited the prime
minister to dine.

06:10.117 --> 06:12.584
I will be with George when
he's sworn into Parliament.

06:12.585 --> 06:13.884
And where will you be?

06:13.885 --> 06:17.216
With your dirt-farmer husband
on your drab little farm,

06:17.217 --> 06:21.083
tapping out stories to justify
your dreary existence.

06:21.084 --> 06:23.818
I call <i>that</i> pathetic.

06:27.551 --> 06:30.151
I am so looking forward to tonight.

06:34.618 --> 06:36.718
(MID-TEMPO MUSIC PLAYING)

06:55.718 --> 06:57.817
(INDISTINCT CONVERSATIONS)

06:57.818 --> 06:59.351
Oh, bloody hell.

07:00.651 --> 07:03.517
Oh, perhaps I should hang back, Doctor.

07:03.518 --> 07:04.517
Come on.

07:04.518 --> 07:06.150
- Roy.
- Oh.

07:06.151 --> 07:09.217
ROY: Have a gander at the
wowser brigade down there.

07:10.052 --> 07:12.417
Hey, whose idea was this?

07:12.418 --> 07:13.884
JACK: I wouldn't have a clue.

07:13.885 --> 07:15.917
(CHUCKLES) Doris.

07:15.918 --> 07:17.317
Mr. Briggs.

07:17.318 --> 07:20.550
I feel safer now between two burly men.

07:20.551 --> 07:24.116
Oh, Mrs. Carvolth and little Emma.

07:24.117 --> 07:26.183
Now, are you feeling any better now?

07:26.184 --> 07:27.584
- EMMA: Yes.
- DORIS: Good.

07:27.585 --> 07:30.585
Hey. You got something to do
with this truck being here?

07:32.618 --> 07:34.216
I thought I told you to clear off.

07:34.217 --> 07:35.951
Goes for some of you others too.

07:35.952 --> 07:37.817
We've got as much right
to be here as anyone.

07:37.818 --> 07:39.917
He's got you all backing
up his pet Commie.

07:39.918 --> 07:42.984
Missy's about as Red as you're
a copper's bootlace, son.

07:42.985 --> 07:44.417
Take that down.

07:44.418 --> 07:47.084
Roy Briggs. Inciting riot.

07:47.618 --> 07:52.116
Mr. Briggs is simply defending
an absolutely powerless woman.

07:52.117 --> 07:53.317
And Doris Collins.

07:53.318 --> 07:55.183
She was warned off and
came back with a mob.

07:55.184 --> 07:57.216
I did no such thing!

07:57.217 --> 07:58.884
DAWN: Haven't you got
something more important

07:58.885 --> 07:59.917
to be getting on with?

07:59.918 --> 08:01.116
Is there a problem?

08:01.117 --> 08:02.083
Mr. Bligh.

08:02.084 --> 08:03.918
Glad you made it, George.

08:04.685 --> 08:05.918
There's your platform.

08:08.718 --> 08:10.817
I let him know his
constituents might appreciate

08:10.818 --> 08:12.484
a bit of a speech.

08:13.885 --> 08:16.184
Well, thank you.

08:16.651 --> 08:18.450
Thank you all for being here.

08:18.451 --> 08:19.417
MAN: Good on you, George.

08:19.418 --> 08:21.283
You know, it's as exciting for me

08:21.284 --> 08:26.083
to entertain our prime minister
as it is for you to greet him.

08:26.084 --> 08:29.784
And I know that you'll give him
a-a real Inverness welcome.

08:29.785 --> 08:31.684
Three cheers for our next MP!

08:31.685 --> 08:32.585
- Hip, hip!
- Hooray!

08:32.650 --> 08:33.650
- Hip, hip!
- Hooray!

08:33.751 --> 08:35.350
- Hip, hip!
- Hooray!

08:35.351 --> 08:37.817
(CHEERS AND APPLAUSE)

08:37.818 --> 08:39.083
Thank you.

08:43.784 --> 08:45.550
Jack.

08:45.551 --> 08:47.216
- Thank you, Roy.
- Mr. Bligh.

08:47.217 --> 08:48.150
Mrs. Collins.

08:48.151 --> 08:50.216
Oh, it's an absolute thrill, Mr. Bligh.

08:50.217 --> 08:53.884
But are you aware that this man
is trying to drive us away?

08:53.885 --> 08:55.317
Sergeant?

08:55.318 --> 08:57.817
I suspect there's an element
out to cause trouble

08:57.818 --> 08:59.585
for Mr. Menzies.

09:01.351 --> 09:02.985
A private word.

09:05.551 --> 09:08.017
- I'm just doing my duty, sir.
- By harassing my constituents?

09:08.018 --> 09:10.151
- Mrs. Bligh said...
- Mrs. Bligh?

09:10.685 --> 09:12.884
She had reason to believe
there'd be a disturbance.

09:12.885 --> 09:14.150
And then there's the petition.

09:14.151 --> 09:15.618
For?

09:16.184 --> 09:17.917
Some of the parents complained

09:17.918 --> 09:19.551
about things being taught at school.

09:20.918 --> 09:22.183
Commie things.

09:22.184 --> 09:24.116
Things against the good Lord.

09:24.117 --> 09:26.818
Others opposed them with a
petition supporting her.

09:27.551 --> 09:31.183
So this has something to do with Mrs.
Nordmann's time teaching?

09:31.184 --> 09:32.150
Yeah.

09:32.151 --> 09:35.618
And... my wife encouraged you?

09:36.217 --> 09:38.083
Just said to keep an eye out.

09:38.084 --> 09:40.216
Wanted the day to go
as smooth as possible.

09:40.217 --> 09:41.216
Mm.

09:41.217 --> 09:45.317
Sergeant, any harassing
of any of the crowd,

09:45.318 --> 09:46.952
and you will have me to answer to.

09:48.484 --> 09:50.484
Is that understood?

09:54.851 --> 09:56.117
Good.

10:00.851 --> 10:03.817
Thank you again for being
here, and enjoy your day.

10:03.818 --> 10:05.918
All of you enjoy your day.

10:07.618 --> 10:09.283
Vote for the Country Party!

10:09.284 --> 10:10.483
MAN: Yeah!

10:10.484 --> 10:11.951
WOMAN: Vote Bligh!

10:11.952 --> 10:14.117
MAN: Good on you, Mr. Bligh!

10:14.918 --> 10:16.551
You were saying something, weren't you?

10:21.018 --> 10:23.117
Doesn't it look marvelous?

10:23.718 --> 10:26.885
The sitting room. Now.

10:40.885 --> 10:42.651
Close the door.

10:47.318 --> 10:49.017
Has Anna said something?

10:49.018 --> 10:49.951
Anna?

10:49.952 --> 10:51.717
She was most unpleasant earlier.

10:51.718 --> 10:52.850
I put her in her place.

10:52.851 --> 10:55.651
Sarah and Sergeant Taylor.

10:56.351 --> 10:57.718
What about them?

10:58.885 --> 11:00.650
Taylor said you encouraged him

11:00.651 --> 11:05.651
to keep her supporters from the
gate as possible agitators.

11:06.518 --> 11:08.684
Reds <i>are</i> amongst us,

11:08.685 --> 11:11.318
and Jews have a long history
as Communist sympathizers.

11:11.818 --> 11:14.117
She was also asked to leave
the school for blasphemy.

11:15.284 --> 11:17.217
I felt better safe than sorry.

11:17.751 --> 11:21.884
If I find you causing
mischief for Sarah again,

11:21.885 --> 11:24.184
you will be out on your ear.

11:25.284 --> 11:26.383
You... You don't... You don't...

11:26.384 --> 11:28.417
Good thing about morphine...

11:28.418 --> 11:31.885
You're more likely to
express your true feelings.

11:38.418 --> 11:40.483
Play your agreed role.

11:40.484 --> 11:42.551
Never presume to play me.

12:00.151 --> 12:03.151
Uh, we'll take him
through to the far room.

12:03.885 --> 12:05.317
Why is he being moved here?

12:05.318 --> 12:06.884
He's a friend of mine.

12:06.885 --> 12:08.051
What happened to him?

12:08.052 --> 12:09.851
Car accident.

12:11.985 --> 12:14.117
VIP treatment.

12:15.551 --> 12:16.584
(EXHALES DEEPLY)

12:16.585 --> 12:17.917
SARAH: Thank you.

12:17.918 --> 12:19.151
Thanks.

12:20.018 --> 12:21.618
Just hang in there, mate.

12:23.551 --> 12:24.952
Pain?

12:25.551 --> 12:26.952
Yes.

12:29.217 --> 12:32.350
Wonder if he'd be so
friendly if he knew.

12:32.351 --> 12:33.884
No one needs to know.

12:33.885 --> 12:35.785
You're safe from that here.

12:38.018 --> 12:39.284
Why are you doing this?

12:41.351 --> 12:43.250
That sounded ungrateful. Sorry.

12:43.251 --> 12:45.351
No. It's a fair question. I...

12:48.818 --> 12:51.484
A man I knew was abandoned in hospital.

12:52.018 --> 12:53.052
Is he okay now?

12:53.751 --> 12:55.517
He died.

12:55.518 --> 12:57.817
Let me get you something for that pain.

12:57.818 --> 12:59.650
James Bligh.

12:59.651 --> 13:00.618
What about him?

13:05.018 --> 13:07.618
There's no reason for him
to know that you're here.

13:08.551 --> 13:10.518
Can we keep it like that?

13:11.551 --> 13:12.917
If he found out how this happened...

13:12.918 --> 13:15.618
He'd be glad you're being looked after.

13:20.117 --> 13:21.918
How's Livvy?

13:22.818 --> 13:24.618
Trying her best.

13:25.885 --> 13:26.817
(SIGHS)

13:26.818 --> 13:29.217
What's so sad is we both
still love each other.

13:31.284 --> 13:32.584
Gino?

13:32.585 --> 13:34.183
He's good.

13:34.184 --> 13:37.216
I'm surprised that still
fits, all that pasta.

13:37.217 --> 13:38.917
You can't talk.

13:38.918 --> 13:42.685
Is that a little, um, spread
I see around your middle?

13:44.551 --> 13:45.917
Too much room service.

13:45.918 --> 13:47.517
You dined in a lot?

13:47.518 --> 13:49.750
Two men dining out? It's
rather obvious, isn't it?

13:49.751 --> 13:52.483
They do it all the time
in gentlemen's clubs.

13:52.484 --> 13:54.483
The way we are, it might show.

13:54.484 --> 13:57.018
You're hardly wearing feather boas.

13:58.818 --> 14:01.217
Henry says I'm overly sensitive.

14:02.084 --> 14:06.484
He's training me in the subtle
art of avoiding attention.

14:09.018 --> 14:10.617
What?

14:10.618 --> 14:11.951
What a conversation to have

14:11.952 --> 14:13.717
before meeting the prime minister.

14:13.718 --> 14:15.550
(MID-TEMPO MUSIC PLAYS)

14:15.551 --> 14:17.550
If he only knew.

14:17.551 --> 14:19.618
(CHEERS AND APPLAUSE)

14:27.151 --> 14:29.216
Doris Collins, Dame Pattie!

14:29.217 --> 14:30.817
President of the CWA!

14:30.818 --> 14:33.083
Good on you, Bob! (LAUGHS)

14:33.084 --> 14:35.151
(DOWN-TEMPO MUSIC PLAYS)

14:52.518 --> 14:54.518
(MUSIC CONTINUES)

15:21.551 --> 15:23.150
Oh. Is Dr. Duncan in attendance?

15:23.151 --> 15:24.350
Oh, Mrs. Bligh.

15:24.351 --> 15:26.017
Sarah.

15:26.018 --> 15:26.917
Elizabeth.

15:26.918 --> 15:29.918
Uh, Mr. Cole to X-ray, please.

15:30.551 --> 15:31.550
How lovely to see you.

15:31.551 --> 15:34.551
How lovely to see <i>you on
the road to recovery.</i>

15:35.351 --> 15:37.418
We have much to catch up on.

15:41.151 --> 15:43.717
Is taking on Regina wise?

15:43.718 --> 15:45.483
You <i>are</i> still recovering.

15:45.484 --> 15:48.317
I intend to pull her
claws or die trying...

15:48.318 --> 15:50.350
possibly literally.

15:50.351 --> 15:53.150
Pardon me. I'm on a
very precise schedule.

15:53.151 --> 15:55.117
I trust she's causing you no harm.

15:56.318 --> 15:58.684
That requires a much
longer conversation,

15:58.685 --> 16:01.350
and... one I'd like to have.

16:01.351 --> 16:02.684
We've 10 minutes.

16:02.685 --> 16:04.717
We'd barely scratch the surface.

16:04.718 --> 16:06.551
(DOOR OPENS)

16:09.052 --> 16:12.817
Well, look at you,
gussied up for battle.

16:12.818 --> 16:14.750
The latest in flak jackets.

16:14.751 --> 16:16.818
I gather Carolyn telephoned.

16:17.618 --> 16:19.951
It was time you made an honest
woman of her, as they say.

16:19.952 --> 16:21.584
- Congratulations.
- I'll leave you to it.

16:21.585 --> 16:22.684
How did it go?

16:22.685 --> 16:24.083
Uh, we made our point.

16:24.084 --> 16:25.283
When you're settled.

16:25.284 --> 16:26.551
We shall speak.

16:29.551 --> 16:31.150
You were at Ash Park, I hear.

16:31.151 --> 16:32.617
I gather you saw him.

16:32.618 --> 16:34.283
(DOWN-TEMPO MUSIC PLAYS)

16:34.284 --> 16:35.718
I should have throttled him.

16:36.284 --> 16:37.885
The man is mine.

16:50.351 --> 16:53.151
Are we sure he wasn't bashed?

16:53.751 --> 16:56.850
I took a look at the
bruising on his back.

16:56.851 --> 16:59.751
Apparently the car rolled twice.

17:00.351 --> 17:02.318
I'll take over from here.

17:04.483 --> 17:05.917
Thank you.

17:10.917 --> 17:12.917
(MUSIC CONTINUES)

17:18.417 --> 17:19.584
MAN: Homo!

17:19.585 --> 17:21.083
Bloody faggot! Poof!

17:21.084 --> 17:21.884
Pervert!

17:21.885 --> 17:23.150
You homo!

17:23.151 --> 17:25.282
Kill him! Faggot!

17:25.284 --> 17:26.317
Kill the faggot!

17:26.318 --> 17:27.951
- (EXHALES SHARPLY)
- Pervert!

17:27.952 --> 17:30.284
(INDISTINCT SHOUTING)

17:31.184 --> 17:32.584
(GASPS)

17:32.585 --> 17:34.216
It's all right.

17:34.217 --> 17:36.750
- It's all right.
- (BREATHING HEAVILY)

17:36.751 --> 17:38.951
It's all right. It's all right.

17:38.952 --> 17:40.384
It's all right.

17:42.184 --> 17:43.618
It's all right.

17:50.952 --> 17:52.550
It should be me having a go at him.

17:52.551 --> 17:54.417
Jack, listen.

17:54.418 --> 17:57.617
It shows more strength
respecting Carolyn's wishes.

17:57.618 --> 18:00.917
And I can dress him down
with fewer consequences.

18:00.918 --> 18:01.884
Now, I must go.

18:01.885 --> 18:05.618
It's essential that I arrive
precisely as dinner is called.

18:12.451 --> 18:14.750
Sir Richard wasn't exaggerating.

18:14.751 --> 18:16.617
Quite the property.

18:16.618 --> 18:17.951
I'm very fortunate, sir.

18:17.952 --> 18:19.884
In more ways than one, eh, George?

18:19.885 --> 18:21.818
(WOMEN LAUGHING)

18:23.751 --> 18:26.850
Dear Anna, the artist of the family,

18:26.851 --> 18:28.450
quite the budding author.

18:28.451 --> 18:30.750
Olivia embraces the
more traditional values

18:30.751 --> 18:32.216
of home and hearth.

18:32.217 --> 18:34.684
I think the modern woman
can aspire to both.

18:34.685 --> 18:35.984
As I do.

18:35.985 --> 18:37.784
Well said, Dame Pattie.

18:37.785 --> 18:38.917
Shall we join the men?

18:38.918 --> 18:40.184
Deirdre?

18:43.551 --> 18:44.750
I may vomit.

18:44.751 --> 18:47.550
She does rather hog the limelight.

18:47.551 --> 18:50.017
Perfect word. Hog.

18:50.018 --> 18:51.150
(CHUCKLES)

18:51.151 --> 18:52.183
(BELL CHIMES)

18:52.184 --> 18:53.550
Time to go in.

18:53.551 --> 18:55.718
Shall we lead the way, my darling?

18:57.351 --> 18:58.784
You're a corker.

18:58.785 --> 19:00.417
I am, rather.

19:00.418 --> 19:02.551
(DOWN-TEMPO MUSIC PLAYS)

19:04.551 --> 19:09.617
To think, Mrs. Bligh is using my
parsley for the prime minister.

19:09.618 --> 19:11.984
Oh, would I were a fly on the wall.

19:11.985 --> 19:14.150
Want to watch out for that Mortein.

19:14.151 --> 19:15.784
- Oh, Mr. Briggs.
- (LAUGHS)

19:15.785 --> 19:17.216
Isn't he a wag, Dawn?

19:17.217 --> 19:19.618
Oh, that he is.

19:20.117 --> 19:22.283
Do my eyes deceive me?

19:22.284 --> 19:23.917
Mrs. Bligh!

19:23.918 --> 19:25.684
- The mother of our Member!
- (APPLAUSE)

19:25.685 --> 19:26.817
Oh!

19:26.818 --> 19:28.584
Oh, and looking so well!

19:28.585 --> 19:29.584
Welcome home.

19:29.585 --> 19:30.951
Thank you, Mrs. Collins.

19:30.952 --> 19:32.717
They'll be thrilled to see you!

19:32.718 --> 19:34.884
(CHUCKLES) Oh, not everyone.

19:34.885 --> 19:36.952
(MUSIC CONTINUES)

19:41.818 --> 19:45.083
He'll need a few days in
here to be on the safe side.

19:45.084 --> 19:46.818
Then home nursing should do.

19:47.484 --> 19:48.850
Nowhere to go.

19:48.851 --> 19:51.483
That's all been organized.

19:51.484 --> 19:52.483
Who am I staying with?

19:52.484 --> 19:55.884
I'll make up the annex where I live...
with Roy Briggs.

19:55.885 --> 19:57.151
Does he know?

19:58.318 --> 20:01.117
He knows you're hurt, and
there's a job for you.

20:03.151 --> 20:04.483
I'm tired.

20:04.484 --> 20:05.851
Sleep.

20:10.484 --> 20:13.818
- DAME PATTIE: Charming house.
- MENZIES: It certainly is.

20:15.885 --> 20:18.550
Anna's husband was unable to join us,

20:18.551 --> 20:20.417
so our table is somewhat askew.

20:20.418 --> 20:23.951
- Not ill health, I hope.
- Oh, slight indisposition.

20:23.952 --> 20:26.017
Have we found our places?

20:26.018 --> 20:28.283
- RICHARD: We have indeed.
- I, uh, I won't interrupt.

20:28.284 --> 20:30.550
I simply want to mention that I'm home

20:30.551 --> 20:32.116
and to wish you all bon appÃ©tit.

20:32.117 --> 20:33.350
Mother!

20:33.351 --> 20:35.384
I hope my arrival is not inconvenient.

20:36.585 --> 20:39.216
Elizabeth, how lovely to see you.

20:39.217 --> 20:40.817
We were concerned about your health.

20:40.818 --> 20:43.717
Rumors of my infirmity
are greatly exaggerated.

20:43.718 --> 20:46.250
Prime Minister, my mother.

20:46.251 --> 20:48.817
Pattie has often spoken of you.

20:48.818 --> 20:50.550
You must join us.

20:50.551 --> 20:52.216
GEORGE: Yes, Mother.

20:52.217 --> 20:54.483
The journey <i>has</i> left me a tad peckish.

20:54.484 --> 20:56.885
If it wouldn't disrupt your plans.

20:58.117 --> 21:00.951
There. Now your table is balanced.

21:00.952 --> 21:02.083
What could be better?

21:02.084 --> 21:04.018
ELIZABETH: (CHUCKLES)

21:04.952 --> 21:06.483
Another setting.

21:06.484 --> 21:08.151
(MID-TEMPO MUSIC PLAYING)

21:09.851 --> 21:11.017
Uh, Olivia, dear,

21:11.018 --> 21:13.116
perhaps you remain next
to the prime minister.

21:13.117 --> 21:16.551
I'm sure he'd enjoy a youthful
perspective on matters.

21:17.018 --> 21:19.617
Isn't this wonderful? (CHUCKLES)

21:19.618 --> 21:21.383
So much more than I expected.

21:21.384 --> 21:23.918
It's wonderful to have you back, Mother.

21:25.751 --> 21:26.617
Darling?

21:26.618 --> 21:28.551
(DOWN-TEMPO MUSIC PLAYS)

21:34.551 --> 21:36.985
I think we can all be seated, then.

21:41.484 --> 21:44.483
Uh, Sir Richard, if I may have a
private moment with you later.

21:44.484 --> 21:47.317
There's a matter on which I
require your particular advice.

21:47.318 --> 21:48.952
Of course.

21:50.217 --> 21:52.884
Well, what could be more perfect?

21:52.885 --> 21:56.216
(MUSIC CONTINUES)

21:56.217 --> 21:58.750
(INSECTS CHIRPING, OWL HOOTING)

21:58.751 --> 22:01.350
(INDISTINCT CONVERSATIONS)

22:01.351 --> 22:03.483
Time we ladies left the gentlemen

22:03.484 --> 22:06.483
to their brandy, cigars,
and mysterious matters.

22:06.484 --> 22:09.150
Oh, let's not impose that
sort of antiquated tomfoolery

22:09.151 --> 22:10.550
on Dame Pattie.

22:10.551 --> 22:12.584
Why don't we all repair
to the sitting room?

22:12.585 --> 22:14.617
Unless the prime minister objects.

22:14.618 --> 22:17.216
Your mother is a progressive, George.

22:17.217 --> 22:18.684
Only recently.

22:18.685 --> 22:20.750
We have a woman on the throne.

22:20.751 --> 22:22.183
I think it's high time we shared

22:22.184 --> 22:23.951
in the after-dinner
conversation, don't you?

22:23.952 --> 22:26.018
- Brava, Grandmother.
- Thank you, dear.

22:26.985 --> 22:29.017
Uh, perhaps I might
retain you, Sir Richard,

22:29.018 --> 22:30.317
and we'll have that private moment.

22:30.318 --> 22:31.584
Why not?

22:31.585 --> 22:34.350
Regina, dear, I look forward
to a good catch-up.

22:34.351 --> 22:37.117
As do I, dear.

22:38.284 --> 22:40.685
I want a balloon of your
best ready, George.

22:41.217 --> 22:42.917
Rest assured.

22:42.918 --> 22:44.517
(CLOCK CHIMING)

22:44.518 --> 22:46.084
Girls, you may close the doors, please.

22:49.651 --> 22:53.484
(CHUCKLES) Well, you showed
who's still lady of the manor.

22:54.484 --> 22:55.684
I did.

22:55.685 --> 22:59.052
Reggie's spitting silent chips.
(CHUCKLES)

23:00.851 --> 23:02.918
So, what can I do for you?

23:03.484 --> 23:06.483
You can explain how you thought
you could rape my daughter

23:06.484 --> 23:08.052
and suffer no consequences.

23:08.851 --> 23:09.817
Ah.

23:09.818 --> 23:11.684
Did you imagine that as her mother,

23:11.685 --> 23:13.417
I would spare you this conversation?

23:13.418 --> 23:17.150
Well, she's crying innocent
because her boyfriend turned up.

23:17.151 --> 23:20.183
Your girl likes a good
time, and you know it.

23:20.184 --> 23:24.018
You say anything, and the
world will know she's a slut.

23:24.585 --> 23:26.784
She'd come out of it worse than me.

23:26.785 --> 23:29.083
- You filth!
- Jesus Christ! Bloody woman!

23:29.084 --> 23:31.951
You vile, rutting pig!

23:31.952 --> 23:33.083
How dare you.

23:33.084 --> 23:35.551
(GRUNTS)

23:37.217 --> 23:38.650
You say the knife slipped,

23:38.651 --> 23:41.052
or I will tell the prime
minister everything.

23:43.484 --> 23:44.483
Accident!

23:44.484 --> 23:45.717
Quickly!

23:45.718 --> 23:46.850
RICHARD: Aah!

23:46.851 --> 23:49.684
You stay away from Carolyn <i>and</i> Anna,

23:49.685 --> 23:51.551
or next time I will geld you.

23:55.923 --> 23:58.089
(INSECTS CHIRPING)

23:58.090 --> 24:00.923
(DOWN-TEMPO MUSIC PLAYS)

24:02.090 --> 24:04.356
So much blood.

24:06.289 --> 24:09.089
Dr. Bell is the night
doctor, but most competent.

24:09.090 --> 24:10.089
You sure we shouldn't have Jack in?

24:10.090 --> 24:11.822
Not that Dr. Bell doesn't
have any experience.

24:11.823 --> 24:14.422
ELIZABETH: No. He'll
telephone, if needs be.

24:15.123 --> 24:16.489
George.

24:16.990 --> 24:18.588
Has the prime minister left?

24:18.589 --> 24:21.389
Yes. He wants to be kept informed.

24:27.389 --> 24:29.321
Bolting the stable door, perhaps,

24:29.322 --> 24:32.356
but the girls must dull those knives.

24:33.322 --> 24:34.389
Are you all right?

24:35.556 --> 24:38.122
ELIZABETH: Trying to remain calm.

24:38.123 --> 24:39.555
GEORGE: We're so sorry.

24:39.556 --> 24:41.289
DEIRDRE: Oh, it's no one's fault.

24:44.223 --> 24:46.522
Perhaps you should take
your grandmother home.

24:46.523 --> 24:47.922
Might be wisest.

24:47.923 --> 24:49.555
Come on, Grandmother.
Let's get you home.

24:49.556 --> 24:53.056
ELIZABETH: James, I will let you
know if I'm feeling unwell.

24:53.556 --> 24:55.321
Oh, Doctor. How's the patient?

24:55.322 --> 24:59.055
The wound has been sutured...
about 20 stitches.

24:59.056 --> 25:01.355
GEORGE: Well, they're more than
welcome to stay if need be.

25:01.356 --> 25:02.822
DR. BELL: He's well bandaged up.

25:02.823 --> 25:04.855
I suggest he sees a surgeon in the city

25:04.856 --> 25:06.855
to assess possible tendon damage.

25:06.856 --> 25:08.922
GEORGE: Perhaps Henry.

25:08.923 --> 25:10.955
The man saved my life.

25:10.956 --> 25:12.056
He's a top-notch surgeon.

25:13.923 --> 25:15.122
May I go in?

25:15.123 --> 25:16.555
He'll be out in a moment.

25:16.556 --> 25:19.356
He asked for a quick word with Mrs.
Bligh.

25:19.956 --> 25:21.556
Of course.

25:22.023 --> 25:25.789
No doubt concerned with the
effect it's had on you.

25:25.790 --> 25:27.523
So thoughtful.

25:30.422 --> 25:33.623
I've prescribed something
to help him sleep.

25:34.123 --> 25:35.756
He might be a little drowsy.

25:38.223 --> 25:39.589
What if I called your bluff?

25:40.157 --> 25:42.321
With the prime minister
and your wife there?

25:42.322 --> 25:44.056
I think not.

25:44.523 --> 25:45.489
What now?

25:46.123 --> 25:47.688
Books are meant to be balanced?

25:47.689 --> 25:49.421
An eye for an eye.

25:49.422 --> 25:51.321
Good Old Testament justice.

25:51.322 --> 25:52.855
Better than none.

25:52.856 --> 25:54.522
You old hypocrite.

25:54.523 --> 25:57.089
You treated your daughter
like a slut for decades,

25:57.090 --> 25:59.122
and you exiled her from
the family for it.

25:59.123 --> 26:02.023
I only gave her one night of shame.

26:02.756 --> 26:05.455
This must be why you
never won best mother

26:05.456 --> 26:07.055
at the Royal Easter Show.

26:07.056 --> 26:10.289
(DOWN-TEMPO MUSIC PLAYING)

26:16.756 --> 26:19.157
You want Old Testament justice?

26:21.589 --> 26:24.421
"I am a fierce and vengeful God."

26:24.422 --> 26:27.023
Oh, you loathsome creature.

26:30.623 --> 26:31.755
DEIRDRE: Oh, Richard.

26:31.756 --> 26:34.755
Oh, don't carry on, Deirdre.
I'll be right as rain.

26:34.756 --> 26:36.756
(KNOCK ON DOOR)

26:37.790 --> 26:40.055
Excuse me, ma'am.

26:40.056 --> 26:41.455
We've cleared away.

26:41.456 --> 26:43.556
Is there anything else that needs doing?

26:44.056 --> 26:46.889
Not until the others return.

26:46.890 --> 26:49.256
We've got Mrs. Bligh's room all ready.

26:49.257 --> 26:50.823
I am Mrs. Bligh.

26:51.956 --> 26:55.688
Always refer to her as Mrs. Bligh Sr.

26:55.689 --> 26:57.422
She is the elder.

26:58.356 --> 26:59.556
She's old.

27:04.556 --> 27:07.055
Factions will be forming.

27:07.056 --> 27:09.090
I trust I can rely upon you.

27:11.356 --> 27:13.923
After all I've done for
you, you would hesitate?

27:14.422 --> 27:16.421
No, ma'am.

27:16.422 --> 27:17.223
Good.

27:19.223 --> 27:22.123
I'll remind you of that
should it become necessary.

27:24.190 --> 27:25.157
You may go.

27:31.422 --> 27:33.355
(DOOR CLOSES)

27:33.356 --> 27:35.589
(DOWN-TEMPO MUSIC PLAYING)

28:06.123 --> 28:08.190
(EXHALES DEEPLY)

28:20.890 --> 28:22.656
(ECHOING) Regina.

28:25.689 --> 28:27.622
Regina.

28:27.623 --> 28:29.388
(MUSIC CONTINUES)

28:29.389 --> 28:30.990
Regina.

28:34.956 --> 28:36.422
Regina.

28:37.589 --> 28:39.022
Oh.

28:39.023 --> 28:41.488
Oh, I must have dozed off.

28:41.489 --> 28:42.588
How is he?

28:42.589 --> 28:44.189
He's on his way home.

28:44.190 --> 28:46.622
More concerned for Mother than himself.

28:46.623 --> 28:48.222
Is he?

28:48.223 --> 28:49.822
You should get to bed.

28:49.823 --> 28:51.322
In time.

28:52.556 --> 28:54.890
You know she did it deliberately.

28:55.756 --> 28:57.755
She knew what the evening meant to me,

28:57.756 --> 28:59.522
and she invaded it.

28:59.523 --> 29:00.922
I asked her back home...

29:00.923 --> 29:03.789
She timed her arrival perfectly.

29:03.790 --> 29:06.089
Playing the fragile flower,

29:06.090 --> 29:08.522
to see me relegated to
the middle of the table

29:08.523 --> 29:11.122
across from your brat of a daughter.

29:11.123 --> 29:12.089
Regina.

29:12.090 --> 29:13.789
(CHUCKLES)

29:13.790 --> 29:14.755
No!

29:14.756 --> 29:16.989
You've drunk too much.

29:16.990 --> 29:18.922
(CHUCKLES)

29:18.923 --> 29:21.321
I've sipped too much.

29:21.322 --> 29:22.122
Have you...

29:22.123 --> 29:26.023
As you say, George, morphine
loosens the tongue.

29:26.556 --> 29:29.756
You want it all your own way, don't you?

29:30.389 --> 29:31.388
Good night.

29:31.389 --> 29:33.990
You will stay, and you will listen.

29:34.756 --> 29:38.489
I have loved you for years.

29:39.389 --> 29:40.688
You've known it.

29:40.689 --> 29:42.288
You must have.

29:42.289 --> 29:44.756
You knew it when you
suggested our arrangement.

29:45.289 --> 29:47.688
But who cares about my feelings?

29:47.689 --> 29:49.090
I'm simply useful.

29:50.689 --> 29:54.321
Then, in your drugged stupor,
when you made love to me,

29:54.322 --> 29:55.722
what did you do?

29:55.723 --> 29:59.355
You retreated into your
infatuation with the Jew.

29:59.356 --> 30:02.688
It was as if you'd fouled yourself.

30:02.689 --> 30:05.688
Well, I have news for you, George.

30:05.689 --> 30:08.455
You are married to me.

30:08.456 --> 30:10.455
And you do need me.

30:10.456 --> 30:14.156
And you will treat me with
respect and never disgust,

30:14.157 --> 30:18.421
or I will pull your entire
world down around your ears,

30:18.422 --> 30:19.989
brick by brick!

30:19.990 --> 30:20.955
Stop now.

30:20.956 --> 30:22.789
I will tell the truth of your son.

30:22.790 --> 30:25.488
I will harass Elizabeth
into an early grave,

30:25.489 --> 30:29.022
and I will announce
you've sired a bastard!

30:29.023 --> 30:29.756
Enough!

30:33.289 --> 30:34.756
Enough!

30:37.123 --> 30:39.289
How do you know?

30:40.322 --> 30:44.488
I-I stumbled over the
codicil to your will.

30:44.489 --> 30:45.889
You went through my papers?

30:45.890 --> 30:47.257
I had no choice.

30:47.823 --> 30:49.023
Where is the morphine?

30:50.823 --> 30:52.157
Where is it?!

30:54.723 --> 30:55.688
Who knows?

30:55.689 --> 30:57.123
No one.

30:59.923 --> 31:04.689
All I did for tonight, and you
let your mother humiliate me.

31:07.223 --> 31:12.422
I offer you love... and
you prefer that woman.

31:14.956 --> 31:18.223
I suffer abuse from your family.

31:21.190 --> 31:24.522
(VOICE BREAKING) It's no
wonder my heart is broken.

31:24.523 --> 31:26.923
(DOWN-TEMPO MUSIC PLAYING)

31:29.923 --> 31:32.189
I will gather the family tomorrow,

31:32.190 --> 31:34.990
and we will deal with
this once and for all.

31:35.756 --> 31:37.156
I am your wife.

31:37.157 --> 31:39.023
The dayroom at 8:00.

31:39.689 --> 31:41.756
Keep your distance from Mother.

31:44.956 --> 31:46.890
(DOOR OPENS)

31:48.756 --> 31:50.355
(KNOCK ON DOOR)

31:50.356 --> 31:51.689
Yes?

31:54.356 --> 31:57.455
A family conference in
the dayroom at 8:00.

31:57.456 --> 31:59.321
There are matters that need resolving.

31:59.322 --> 32:00.256
Olivia?

32:00.257 --> 32:01.755
Rose is informing her.

32:01.756 --> 32:04.689
A driver is taking a
message to Anna and Gino.

32:05.090 --> 32:06.023
Good night.

32:09.723 --> 32:11.055
- Mother?
- Hm?

32:11.056 --> 32:13.489
Could you be in the dayroom at 8:00?

32:13.990 --> 32:16.090
It's time we had everything
out in the open.

32:16.623 --> 32:18.189
Regarding?

32:18.190 --> 32:21.488
How we all proceed in this
disaster of my making.

32:21.489 --> 32:23.622
- Of <i>your</i> making?
- I married the woman.

32:23.623 --> 32:26.122
I take ultimate responsibility.

32:26.123 --> 32:28.923
I've asked Regina to keep
a distance till then.

32:29.422 --> 32:31.190
I ask the same of you.

32:35.756 --> 32:38.123
(TELEPHONE RINGING)

32:43.689 --> 32:44.722
(CLEARS THROAT)

32:44.723 --> 32:46.689
Couldn't go to sleep without a kiss?

32:47.823 --> 32:49.089
Carolyn.

32:49.090 --> 32:50.288
Oh!

32:50.289 --> 32:51.855
George, I'm sorry. I thought...

32:51.856 --> 32:53.421
I know I'm presuming,

32:53.422 --> 32:55.288
but a car is collecting
you in half an hour.

32:55.289 --> 32:56.089
Mother?

32:56.090 --> 33:00.022
No, it's nothing to do with
her or to worry about.

33:00.023 --> 33:02.688
A family meeting first
thing in the morning.

33:02.689 --> 33:04.122
I can drive myself.

33:04.123 --> 33:05.523
A car will collect you.

33:07.090 --> 33:08.288
What's happened?

33:08.289 --> 33:11.023
I wouldn't be asking if
it wasn't essential.

33:11.689 --> 33:13.322
We'll talk in the morning.

33:14.923 --> 33:16.823
(DIAL TONE)

33:23.023 --> 33:25.422
(DOWN-TEMPO MUSIC PLAYING)

34:32.822 --> 34:35.223
(DOOR CLOSES)

34:39.223 --> 34:41.090
(SNIFFS)

34:42.322 --> 34:44.289
(UP-TEMPO MUSIC PLAYING)

34:54.356 --> 34:55.688
What's wrong?

34:55.688 --> 34:57.956
Mr. Polson's gone.

34:59.157 --> 35:01.089
(DOG BARKING)

35:01.090 --> 35:02.522
ROY: Sit down!

35:02.523 --> 35:04.889
(DOOR OPENS)

35:04.890 --> 35:07.288
Shut up, you silly mutt.

35:07.289 --> 35:09.722
(GRUNTS)

35:09.723 --> 35:11.456
Missy!

35:11.523 --> 35:12.555
Missy!

35:12.556 --> 35:14.156
(BREATHING HEAVILY)

35:14.157 --> 35:15.755
Harry. Harry.

35:15.756 --> 35:17.355
He can't see me.

35:17.356 --> 35:18.588
He can't.

35:18.589 --> 35:19.756
He can't see me.

35:21.556 --> 35:23.690
(INSECTS CHIRPING)

35:26.122 --> 35:27.689
He was there.

35:27.690 --> 35:29.589
He was right outside the door.

35:29.590 --> 35:31.555
It was an unfortunate coincidence.

35:31.556 --> 35:33.121
I can't see him. Not yet.

35:33.122 --> 35:34.889
Not like this.

35:34.890 --> 35:36.589
They left. No one was admitted.

35:36.590 --> 35:38.722
There's no reason for James to return.

35:38.723 --> 35:40.690
But it's... it's better here.

35:41.489 --> 35:43.889
Can I stay here? Y-You
could look after me.

35:43.890 --> 35:45.855
I have my job, Harry.

35:45.856 --> 35:47.623
You said there's a room.

35:48.356 --> 35:50.323
(SIGHS) It's not ready.

35:53.823 --> 35:55.122
All right.

35:57.222 --> 35:58.822
Sit... Sit down.

35:58.823 --> 36:01.256
(DOWN-TEMPO MUSIC PLAYING)

36:06.823 --> 36:09.956
Dr. Duncan can check you over tomorrow.

36:09.957 --> 36:11.756
If he agrees, fine.

36:12.623 --> 36:14.121
What about you?

36:14.122 --> 36:16.556
I'll manage.

36:17.089 --> 36:19.155
The man who died.

36:19.156 --> 36:20.555
Yes?

36:20.556 --> 36:22.022
He's why you're helping me.

36:22.023 --> 36:23.922
Oh, it's what we nurses do.

36:23.923 --> 36:25.923
Here. Lie down.

36:30.790 --> 36:33.556
I'm doing what I wish
someone had done for him.

36:37.790 --> 36:40.256
How long was he in hospital?

36:42.523 --> 36:44.323
Eight years.

36:44.489 --> 36:46.256
Eight years?

36:47.089 --> 36:48.289
Yes.

36:49.623 --> 36:50.923
Who was he?

36:53.057 --> 36:54.489
My...

36:57.089 --> 36:58.957
The love of my life.

37:01.623 --> 37:04.523
You're helping me as
much as I'm helping you.

37:06.823 --> 37:08.523
Get some rest.

37:10.690 --> 37:11.823
(DOOR CLOSES)

37:14.723 --> 37:16.422
Reckon you might need this.

37:16.423 --> 37:17.889
I should let the hospital know.

37:17.890 --> 37:20.723
- Well, I can go if you like.
- No. It's better it's me.

37:23.023 --> 37:24.890
He tell you why he'd done a bunk?

37:30.389 --> 37:33.155
There are things about him I...
I didn't tell you.

37:33.156 --> 37:36.723
I was waiting... for the right moment.

37:38.590 --> 37:40.790
I hope you can understand.

37:46.122 --> 37:48.156
Harry was beaten...

37:49.556 --> 37:51.156
for being homosexual.

37:54.323 --> 37:55.322
You're kidding me.

37:55.323 --> 37:56.288
- No.
- Nah.

37:56.289 --> 37:57.555
Yes.

37:57.556 --> 37:58.355
Harry's...

37:58.356 --> 37:59.555
Nah. Pull the other one.

37:59.556 --> 38:00.556
He is.

38:01.089 --> 38:02.555
Big, strong bloke like Harry?

38:02.556 --> 38:03.957
Yes.

38:10.389 --> 38:11.723
Struth.

38:18.356 --> 38:20.389
Well, I've never met one before.

38:22.623 --> 38:25.222
You have. You just haven't known it.

38:28.456 --> 38:29.622
James.

38:29.623 --> 38:30.622
James Bligh.

38:30.623 --> 38:32.422
- Yes.
- Now you <i>are</i> having me on.

38:32.423 --> 38:35.221
Harry ran tonight because he
saw James at the hospital.

38:35.222 --> 38:37.489
- James is a married man.
- Yes, but...

38:38.957 --> 38:40.889
As I'm dragging you into
the middle of this,

38:40.890 --> 38:42.923
you deserve the whole truth.

38:45.957 --> 38:47.823
Blokes and blokes.

38:49.122 --> 38:51.288
It's not natural.

38:51.289 --> 38:53.555
If you'd rather Harry didn't
stay, I can't force you.

38:53.556 --> 38:55.755
A-And all this "He
can't see me" stuff...

38:55.756 --> 38:56.823
What's that about?

38:57.890 --> 38:59.622
James and he were
attracted to each other.

38:59.623 --> 39:02.156
I imagine that's why Harry left town.

39:03.189 --> 39:05.690
Things that go on behind a bloke's back.

39:06.790 --> 39:09.556
I should let the hospital know.
They'll be worried.

39:15.556 --> 39:17.289
You want to help him.

39:17.923 --> 39:19.156
He has no one else.

39:19.823 --> 39:22.089
Well, we'll see how it goes, eh?

39:23.723 --> 39:25.923
So long as he doesn't
give <i>me the glad eye.</i>

39:26.890 --> 39:28.389
I think you'll be safe.

39:31.790 --> 39:33.122
Thank you.

39:34.289 --> 39:36.188
(DOOR OPENS, CLOSES)

39:36.189 --> 39:38.923
(MID-TEMPO MUSIC PLAYING)

39:42.323 --> 39:44.256
(INSECTS CHIRPING)

39:49.690 --> 39:51.756
(BRAKE CLICKS, ENGINE SHUTS OFF)

39:53.756 --> 39:55.922
Thank you, Rose.

39:55.923 --> 39:57.322
Sorry to have kept you up.

39:57.323 --> 39:58.322
I don't mind.

39:58.323 --> 39:59.622
(DOOR CLOSES)

39:59.623 --> 40:01.355
Is my mother awake?

40:01.356 --> 40:02.488
She turned in early.

40:02.489 --> 40:05.155
Things have been at sixes and sevens.

40:05.156 --> 40:06.155
I rather gathered.

40:06.156 --> 40:08.023
With Sir Richard and all.

40:09.222 --> 40:12.155
(DOORKNOB RATTLES, KNOCK ON DOOR)

40:12.156 --> 40:13.422
CAROLYN: Mother?

40:13.423 --> 40:14.889
- Oh.
- Mother, it's me.

40:14.890 --> 40:16.155
Coming.

40:16.156 --> 40:17.755
(DOORKNOB RATTLING)

40:17.756 --> 40:19.690
(SNIFFLES, SIGHS)

40:21.222 --> 40:22.823
Oh, Carolyn.

40:23.323 --> 40:24.589
Why is your door locked?

40:24.590 --> 40:26.022
Oh.

40:26.023 --> 40:29.423
It will be locked every
night from now on.

40:30.423 --> 40:34.222
I awoke to the odor of Fleur
de Nuit, Regina's perfume.

40:34.890 --> 40:35.989
She was in your room?

40:35.990 --> 40:37.589
While I was asleep.

40:37.590 --> 40:39.155
That is positively sinister.

40:39.156 --> 40:40.890
Indeed it is.

40:41.489 --> 40:44.488
I assume you're here
at George's summoning.

40:44.489 --> 40:46.556
- Do you have any idea?
- No.

40:48.489 --> 40:50.256
What's this business with Sir Richard?

40:51.489 --> 40:54.023
His fruit knife slipped.

40:54.489 --> 40:56.289
It's a nasty gash.

40:57.356 --> 40:58.823
Clumsy.

40:59.923 --> 41:00.922
Mother.

41:00.923 --> 41:04.488
The vile creature tried
to put the blame on you.

41:04.489 --> 41:06.289
He had the gall to smirk.

41:07.156 --> 41:09.322
It was a moment of impulse.

41:09.323 --> 41:10.122
Mother.

41:10.656 --> 41:12.590
Do you think I'd see him go unpunished?

41:16.089 --> 41:17.923
Thank you.

41:18.423 --> 41:20.356
(SIGHS)

41:21.923 --> 41:24.422
(VOICE BREAKING) I'm so sorry, Carolyn.

41:24.423 --> 41:26.089
What for?

41:28.790 --> 41:32.889
All the years we missed because...

41:32.890 --> 41:35.088
I sat in judgment of you.

41:35.089 --> 41:37.156
(DOWN-TEMPO MUSIC PLAYING)

41:38.389 --> 41:40.656
It's my shame to bear.

41:46.690 --> 41:48.122
Oh. (SIGHS)

41:54.823 --> 41:57.255
(MUSIC CONTINUES)

41:57.256 --> 41:59.222
(BIRDS CHIRPING)

42:06.057 --> 42:09.155
Now, if you can manage
to talk to James...

42:09.156 --> 42:11.488
Let's just see what your
father says first, hmm?

42:11.489 --> 42:13.388
(CLOCK TICKING)

42:13.389 --> 42:15.323
(MUSIC CONTINUES)

43:00.122 --> 43:02.122
(MUSIC CONTINUES)

43:15.823 --> 43:17.422
A minute late.

43:17.423 --> 43:18.957
Apologies.

43:28.023 --> 43:29.555
Now we're all here,

43:29.556 --> 43:32.555
I'd appreciate your full
attention until I'm done.

43:32.556 --> 43:35.922
I am happy to hear anything
you have to say privately.

43:35.923 --> 43:38.555
I will speak frankly and honestly.

43:38.556 --> 43:41.057
Please don't interrupt.

43:42.623 --> 43:44.890
Firstly, Regina.

43:45.756 --> 43:47.355
I have been unfair to you.

43:47.356 --> 43:49.088
You're right in what
you said last night...

43:49.089 --> 43:52.155
I thought more of myself in
marrying than I did of you.

43:52.156 --> 43:56.555
I should have made my
expectations much clearer.

43:56.556 --> 43:57.822
I will do so now

43:57.823 --> 43:59.957
so we all understand the situation.

44:00.756 --> 44:03.355
You're my wife in name only.

44:03.356 --> 44:05.221
You are not the mistress of Ash Park.

44:05.222 --> 44:07.289
- George...
- Be quiet!

44:08.690 --> 44:11.523
There is no mistress of Ash Park.

44:14.957 --> 44:17.022
Mother, I'm glad to see you back,

44:17.023 --> 44:18.889
but the bitterness that
came between us before

44:18.890 --> 44:21.288
could well return if you
assume that role again.

44:21.289 --> 44:24.956
Ash Park will always be your
home, but not your domain.

44:24.957 --> 44:28.288
That is an old concept linked
to the family as it was.

44:28.289 --> 44:31.556
But too much has changed for
us to cling to old concepts.

44:33.222 --> 44:36.121
We're about to have our first divorce,

44:36.122 --> 44:40.089
hopefully with no animosity,
for the sake of Georgie.

44:40.890 --> 44:45.488
We have our first budding
author and winemaker.

44:45.489 --> 44:48.088
And, Gino, I would like
to finance your venture

44:48.089 --> 44:50.288
as an expansion of Bligh interests.

44:50.289 --> 44:51.755
George, I-I would never have asked.

44:51.756 --> 44:53.856
I'm very happy to offer.

44:54.556 --> 44:56.822
And our old maid...

44:56.823 --> 44:58.121
Oh!

44:58.122 --> 45:00.555
is finally embracing respectability,

45:00.556 --> 45:02.956
and her joy is ours.

45:02.957 --> 45:05.890
How thrilled we are.

45:06.890 --> 45:09.522
And now, as head of the family,

45:09.523 --> 45:13.923
I'm taking it on myself to
dictate what happens next.

45:15.023 --> 45:16.623
Mother stays.

45:17.723 --> 45:20.322
I would love Carolyn to move
back to prepare for her wedding,

45:20.323 --> 45:23.989
and I would appreciate Olivia
moving back into the house.

45:23.990 --> 45:26.389
Choice of bedrooms is hers.

45:28.222 --> 45:31.322
And, Regina, we will
move you to the cottage.

45:31.323 --> 45:33.388
It makes you available
leading up to the election,

45:33.389 --> 45:37.689
but it also means that
animosity can be avoided.

45:37.690 --> 45:40.922
I want no more nasty spats in...

45:40.923 --> 45:42.523
in various corners.

45:43.023 --> 45:45.222
That goes for all of you.

45:47.289 --> 45:49.022
How can I hope to help
govern the country

45:49.023 --> 45:51.489
if I can't even govern my own home?

45:56.489 --> 45:58.756
(MID-TEMPO MUSIC PLAYING)

46:05.289 --> 46:07.089
One final thing.

46:10.823 --> 46:14.356
The child that Mrs. Nordmann
is carrying is mine.

46:16.222 --> 46:17.990
I'm about to see her now.

46:19.089 --> 46:21.623
The matter is between the two of us.

46:22.323 --> 46:24.623
Interfere at your peril.

46:27.957 --> 46:29.990
(DOOR OPENS)

46:33.289 --> 46:35.590
(MUSIC CONTINUES)

46:37.590 --> 46:39.489
(ENGINE STARTS)

46:41.690 --> 46:44.057
George!

46:46.489 --> 46:48.723
(UP-TEMPO MUSIC PLAYING)

47:07.523 --> 47:09.523
(ENGINES SHUT OFF)

47:21.790 --> 47:24.089
I think it's time for that talk.

